      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 3929: The tree-walk callback returns `1` for an already-visited object. In libgit2, any non-zero callback return aborts the whole walk, so a valid repository with a shared blob/subtree can either be reported invalid or stop traversal early and miss later corrupt objects. Continue the walk for duplicates instead of aborting it.\n```suggestion\n        if (!ctx-\u003evisited-\u003einsert(*id).second)\n            return 0; // already verified; keep walking the remaining entries\n```",
